MPUMALANGA cops have arrested over 100 for destruction of
property after protests. Thousands of protesters assembled outside the eMbalenhle
Police Station demanding that those who were arrested for public violence and
theft be released. Following that, the police used rubber bullets to disperse
the crowd. Mpumalanga police spokesperson, Leonard Hlathi said on
Tuesday there was attempt to torch the eMbalenhle police station. He added that a mall, post office and filing station were torched.
. “We are saying that even though community members are not
happy with services, the destruction of property is tantamount to criminal
acts. We are calling for calm in this area because if this
continues to happen we will have to arrest more community members,” Hlathi
said. 